article.headline: (11) GEORGIA 92, EASTERN KY 60
article.story:
RICHMOND, Kentucky (Ticker) -- Cori Chambers scored 17 points 
and Christi Thomas had 15 points and 15 rebounds as No. 11
Georgia defeated Eastern Kentucky, 92-60, in the Comfort Suites
Classic.

The Lady Bulldogs led by 18 points at halftime and shot 58
percent (18-for-31) from the field in the second half.

Kara Braxton scored 14 points and Janese Hardrick added 12 for
Georgia (10-2), which has won three straight games after
suffering a 71-58 loss at Texas on December 20.

Sherill Baker contributed 10 points, six assists and three
steals for the Lady Bulldogs, who improved to 4-0 in the
all-time series versus the Lady Colonels.

Katie Kelly netted 18 points to lead Eastern Kentucky (4-6),
which committed 20 turnovers and was outrebounded, 50-33.
